"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-31-stephen-nedoroscik-pommel-horse-olympics-clark-kent\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"On Monday night, Team USA's men's gymnastics team earned their first medal \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 a third-place bronze \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 for the first time since George Bush was in the Oval Office.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999590122579, \"rank\": 4.0954745170207485e-08, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"score\": 0.9999992318592598, \"rank\": 7.681413225004646e-07, \"text\": \"George Bush\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\"}, {\"begin\": 152, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oval_Office\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oval Office\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oval_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oval_Office\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the long-awaited medal moment spoke to the combined talents of the five-person team, it was Pommel Horse Guy's efforts that propelled them to the podium.\\u00c2  Unlike his teammates, Stephen Nedoroscik was the only member of the group to qualify for a single event at the Olympics, the pommel horse, a notoriously difficult event that requires athletes to continuously balance and swing their bodies atop an apparatus with two handles using only their hands (and impressive core strength) to support themselves.\\u00c2  Stephen Nedoroscik had to score big on pommel horse for Team USA in the last rotation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6  AND HE DID.\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999590122579, \"rank\": 4.0954745170207485e-08, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00af  \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00ba: NBC and Peacockpic.twitter.com/hkhiHpovyh  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 NBC Olympics & Paralympics (@NBCOlympics)July 29, 2024    Related  The pommel horse wasn't the only place Nedoroscik gained momentum, however.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999974147613, \"rank\": 2.5853466623078525e-09, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25-year-old quickly found major internet appeal where social media users and Olympic fans homed in on his pre- and post-competition antics, which largely included dozing off on the sidelines until his event turn.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"OUR ROMAN EMPIRE,\\\" wrote NBC Olympics' official Instagram account, alongsidean imageof a seemingly snoozing (or is it meditating?)\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1227, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 1250, \"end\": 1259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.793811202193018e-38, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nedoroscik, a reference to theinternet trendthat went viral in 2023.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are a few things you should know about the internet's latest Olympic obsession.\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally from Worcester, Massachusetts, Nedoroscik studied electrical engineering at Penn State University, where he also competed in gymnastics.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\", \"score\": 0.8813238406679588, \"rank\": 0.134656699220243, \"text\": \"Worcester, Massachusetts\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\"}, {\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\", \"score\": 0.8813238406679588, \"rank\": 0.134656699220243, \"text\": \"Worcester, Massachusetts\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worcester_Tornadoes\"}, {\"begin\": 1576, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"score\": 0.8236461272184689, \"rank\": 0.21411272806706408, \"text\": \"Penn State University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\"}, {\"begin\": 1625, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9999996415031734, \"rank\": 3.5721109284042127e-07, \"text\": \"gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His profession \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and bespectacled appearance \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 earned him the title of \\\"nerdy\\\" from fans across social media.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  After being named to the Olympic team in June, Nederoscik told press that it had long been on his radar to qualify for the Games.\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhen I was very, very young people would tell me, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098One day you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re going to be an Olympian!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said,according to NPR.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBack then I was just a dorky little kid.\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now look at me \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m a dorky adult, going to the Olympics.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  AuthorJohn Greenchimed inon X/Twitter,happy to report that \\\"Stephen Nedoroscik just struck a blow for nerds everywhere.\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2194, \"end\": 2212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beautiful.\\\"\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  \\\"People who are not nerds do not understand how long we have been waiting for an electrical engineer from Pennsylvania to [sic] POMMEL THE HELL OUT OF A HORSE,\\\" Green added ina separate tweet.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"score\": 0.9980971792799407, \"rank\": 0.0019062381155217506, \"text\": \"Pennsylvania\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  To hear it in Green's own words, \\\"To truly understand Stephen Nedoroscik's nerd credentials, you need to know that he is in Paris for the Olympics and posting to his insta story aboutsolving a Rubik's cubein under 10 seconds.\\\"\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2521, \"end\": 2539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1356210468207507e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  To truly understand Stephen Nedoroscik's nerd credentials, you need to know that he is in Paris for the Olympics and posting to his insta story about solving a rubik's cube in under 10 seconds.pic.twitter.com/2vFygJBifW  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 John Green (@sportswithjohn)July 29, 2024    \\u00c2  Nedoroscik, a seeming Rubik's cube aficionado, took to his Instagram account ahead of his team competition to get some cubing time in.\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2718, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 2788, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1356210468207507e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Green\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9227024910328636e-27, \"text\": \"John Green\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 3030, \"end\": 3039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.793811202193018e-38, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s stress relief,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said told TODAY on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSometimes I make the excuse that it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s good for wrist rehab, too.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  CNN reportedthat Nedoroscik's personal record for solving a Rubik's cube is 8.6 seconds.\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The outlet also noted that he dabbles in other forms of puzzling, as well.\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a gymnast friend put him on to \\\"killer sudoku,\\\"\\u00c2\\u00a0 Nedoroscik became the 43rd person in the world to solve a sudoku puzzle that claimed to be the \\\"world's hardest.\\\"\", \"from\": 3406, \"to\": 3575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3444, \"end\": 3457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killer_sudoku\", \"score\": 0.9999961435975601, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"killer sudoku\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killer_sudoku\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killer_sudoku\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  It's a bird!\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a plane!\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's Pommel Horse Guy!\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  Nedoroscik was quickly dubbed the \\\"Clark Kent\\\" of the Games, a reference toSuperman'salter ego with a lackluster bespectacled disguise.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3669, \"end\": 3679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3748057545004936e-51, \"text\": \"Clark Kent\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clips of the athlete ostensibly napping during other apparatus events took place went viral.\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once it was his turn, he whipped off his glasses to demonstrate his mastery of the skill, secured the medal and returned to the sidelines.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00c2  \\u00c2  \\\"I am a goofy guy with glasses on, but as soon as I take them off I am locked in,\\\" Nedorosciktold TODAY.\", \"from\": 3863, \"to\": 4113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  https://www.instagram.com/p/C-DB3VbR6Zp/?hl=en  \\u00c2  Separate from super-hero coded references, the internet also found a way to liken Nedoroscik toKen,whose job in the\\\"Barbie\\\" moviewas infamously just \\\"beach.\\\"\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Given that the Olympian quite literally had one job to perform, it's an apt comparison.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  Obsessed with this guy on the US men's gymnastics team who's only job is pommel horse, so he just sits there until he's activated like a sleeper agent, whips off his glasses like Clark Kent and does a pommel horse routine that helps deliver the team its first medal in 16 years.pic.twitter.com/0D1ZqJjFa1  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Megan \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u009a (@MegWritesBooks)July 29, 2024    \\u00c2  \\u00c2  While speaking on theTODAY broadcast,Nedoroscik tugged on his ear, a special movement he shared was a signal between him and his grandfather, who passed away last year.\", \"from\": 4327, \"to\": 4949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4342, \"end\": 4350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999815759113, \"rank\": 1.842392600261189e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 4450, \"end\": 4452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997911329434677, \"rank\": 0.0002088946628095534, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4599, \"end\": 4609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3748057545004936e-51, \"text\": \"Clark Kent\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\"}, {\"begin\": 4730, \"end\": 4735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"score\": 0.7112776543946616, \"rank\": 0.4059098751631452, \"text\": \"Megan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cdziadziu,\\\" (which means \\\"grandfather\\\" in Polish) served in World War II and was Nedoroscik's \\\"idol.\\\"\", \"from\": 4950, \"to\": 5057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4998, \"end\": 5004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\", \"score\": 0.8244710993514314, \"rank\": 0.1594429781843712, \"text\": \"Polish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve kept the tradition up, and now it always means, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Hey,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 to everyone that I love,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the gymnast said.\", \"from\": 5059, \"to\": 5176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhen I was at Penn State, that was the thing that I did whenever I was on TV to say, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Hey, Dziadziu.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  https://www.instagram.com/p/C-C98P7xosx/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=embed_video_watch_again  \\u00c2  Tess McCracken, Nedoroscik's long-term girlfriend of eight years, was present to watch the moment her boyfriend became a viral sensation and Olympic medalist all in one.\", \"from\": 5177, \"to\": 5564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5194, \"end\": 5204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"score\": 0.9949473495893456, \"rank\": 0.005077873947735429, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was so lightheaded from screaming that I almost fainted,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the 26-year-old told NBC in a phone interview.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  Stephen Nedoroscik, you are an OLYMPIAN\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ba\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8pic.twitter.com/YNN0Q0W3dT  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Tess McCracken (@tess_mccracken)July 1, 2024    \\u00c2  McCracken, who met Nedoroscik at Penn State, described him as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgoofy guy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d who is \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009creally lighthearted\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009calways sees the bright side of things.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBlowing up on the internet has been such an unexpected side effect of this whole adventure,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she added.\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 6090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5651, \"end\": 5654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999974147613, \"rank\": 2.5853466623078525e-09, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 5818, \"end\": 5827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Joy_McCracken\", \"score\": 0.9995426240911858, \"rank\": 0.0004575851972650675, \"text\": \"McCracken\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Joy_McCracken\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Joy_McCracken\"}, {\"begin\": 5851, \"end\": 5861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"score\": 0.9949473495893456, \"rank\": 0.005077873947735429, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have people like tagging me, calling me \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Lois Lane.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m like, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098OK, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m not going to be mad about it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Read more  about this topic  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 6091, \"to\": 6277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6273, \"end\": 6276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999997738446182, \"rank\": 2.2615542722673324e-07, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited.\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6312, \"end\": 6317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.928732955219327e-22, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SALON \\u00c2\\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 6375, \"to\": 6471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6456, \"end\": 6465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 6467, \"end\": 6470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999997738446182, \"rank\": 2.2615542722673324e-07, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbp